Skilled Software Engineer with 3 years of hands-on experience in automation and manual testing. Proficient in Selenium, TestNG, and Rest Assured with a strong track record of reducing manual testing efforts and enhancing software quality. Experienced in
API, ETL, web application, and Database testing techniques. Worked on waterfall and agile methodologies across various teams and clients to deliver reliable software solutions.

professionalExperience.description:
The responsibilities that the position of warehouse lead required, consisted of the supervision of other employees which entailed keeping track of schedules, effectively communicating and assisting employees and management to meet the demands of the company and being able to address concerns and conflict in an appropriate, professional manner. This role requires one to not only be good at the job but to know how to add value and teach others to be just as good . Problem solving and conflict resolution with high energy combined with the ability to be interactive and enthusiastic are key qualities to have in assuming the position.
General Warehouse

This role requires attention to detail and the ability to learn instantaneously how to pick items for customer orders and pack them while following proper warehouse procedures. Tasks often come with different variations such as preserving a clean and orderly workspace, using handheld scanners and computerized operating systems that coincide with inventory, practicing safety procedures, operating machine equipment and working with a team to meet performance standards and productivity goals.

The primary obligations of the job were to assist with online sales. It was important to keep track of inventory and sale performances. To sustain a positive online shopping experience for customer, providing help with any complications and answering questions in a timely, adequate manner were vital.

Amazon.com - Remote
The work from home customer service associate position with Amazon.com requires discipline and enthusiasm to give customers the best online shopping experience. There was an ongoing commitment to answering inbound calls dealing with sales, customer account fixes, and processing returns and refunds all while practicing 100% customer. Successfully doing so, the ability to maintain performance rates of
96% and above came effortlessly.
Cashier/ Customer Service

As a cashier the main duties performed on a day-to-day basis were providing customers with expeditious, friendly, and efficient shopping experience. Regulating transactions, resolving customer issues and delivering results, as well as maintaining a safe and well put together workstation contributed to the responsibilities of the job title.

Operated warehouse equipment including forklifts, pallet jacks, and hand trucks to efficiently move and organize inventory.
 Performed regular inventory checks to ensure accurate stock levels and timely identification of discrepancies.
 Trained new staff on best practices for warehouse operations, enhancing team efficiency and safety compliance.
 Utilized warehouse management software to track inventory movement and generate reports for management.

Conducted thorough quality inspections on ingot production processes to ensure compliance with industry standards.
 Performed dimensional and visual inspections of ingots to identify defects and ensure product integrity.
 Collaborated with production teams to implement corrective actions for non-conformance issues identified during inspections.
 Utilized various testing equipment and techniques to assess the physical and chemical properties of ingots.
 Maintained accurate records of quality control data, including inspection results and non-conformance reports.
 Developed and updated quality assurance protocols to enhance the efficiency of the quality control process.
 Trained new team members on quality standards and inspection procedures to ensure consistency across the team.
 Assisted in the preparation of quality reports for management review, highlighting key findings and areas for improvement.
